                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p31r6nm41/manifest/annotation/p1",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>\n                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <placeName>Curaçao</placeName>\n                <date>9 <sic>Yany</sic> 1856</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Rev Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I am in receipt of your<lb/> valued lines of the <date>2d</date>\n                Ulto. And am happy to per<lb/>ceive from the same your good health &amp; I<lb/>\n                <sic>inclose</sic> you hereby a Bill to your favor for $107.84<lb/> against\n                    <persName>Messrs Bomen Graves &amp; Co</persName>\n                <placeName>N/Y</placeName>, from said<lb/> amt. You will take off for your a/c\n                $74.50 of<lb/> the books which I have sold; and the balance<lb/> of $33. 34 your\n                will oblige me to hand to <persName>Messr<lb/> J. M Moss &amp; Brother</persName>,\n                with the letters <sic>inclosed</sic>.<lb/> I have to conclude for to day for not\n                    <sic>haveing</sic><lb/> time,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">remaining yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">B deCasseres Jr</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>NB.</p>\n            <p>I have wrote you several times<lb/> about the Occident of <date>May</date> which was\n                not received,<lb/> please send them, that I may give to the subscribers<lb/> also\n                please to join with the occident one of <sic>jewish</sic> Ad<lb/>vocate.\n                    <persName>Rev: Choemacieu<add>?</add></persName> send his compliment<lb/> to\n                you.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p31r6nm41/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
